This article is a transcript of a speech given by President Joe Biden at the Delavan Grider Community Center in Buffalo, New York. The President and First Lady visited the center to meet with families affected by a recent shooting at a grocery store. In his speech, President Biden expressed his condolences and solidarity with the families, acknowledging the pain and loss they have experienced. He condemned the ideology of white supremacy and domestic terrorism, stating that hate and fear should not define America. The President called for action to prevent future acts of violence, including keeping assault weapons off the streets and addressing online radicalization. He emphasized the importance of unity and rejecting the ideology of hate. President Biden concluded by expressing hope and determination that America will endure and become a better place to live.